From: chiappa port <chiappa@localhost>
Date: Mon, 11 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm/panel: remarkable-cumulus: select VIDEOMODE_HELPERS

panel-rm-cumulus uses of_get_drm_display_mode() which is compiled only
when CONFIG_VIDEOMODE_HELPERS=y (it sits inside
#ifdef CONFIG_VIDEOMODE_HELPERS in drm_modes.c).  Without this select the
symbol is absent from Module.symvers and modpost rejects the driver.

Every other panel driver that calls of_get_drm_display_mode() already
carries this select; this was simply omitted from the vendor Kconfig.

Signed-off-by: chiappa port <chiappa@localhost>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/panel/Kconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/Kconfig
@@ -623,6 +623,7 @@ config DRM_PANEL_REMARKABLE_CUMULUS
 	tristate "reMarkable cumulus LVDS panel"
 	depends on OF
+	select VIDEOMODE_HELPERS
 	help
 	   Say Y here if you want to enable support for reMarkable
 	   cumulus LVDS panel.
